# ── AI town intelligence (optional) ──────────────────────────────────
# With a key, towns occasionally generate higher-quality conversations,
# story beats and summaries via OpenRouter (each town uses a model
# matching its culture). Without it, deterministic local templates are
# used — the simulation works identically either way.
# Put the real key in .env.local (gitignored), not here.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# ── Realtime presence server (optional — shows "N watching") ────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_REALTIME_URL=http://localhost:3001
REALTIME_PORT=3001

# ── Database (SQLite via node:sqlite, requires Node >= 23) ───────────
DATABASE_PATH=./data/emergence.db

# ── Token-gated rewards (optional, server-side) ──────────────────────
# Set these in your host's environment (e.g. Railway → Variables), never
# in code or a committed file. Only the App ID is public.
#
# Privy (Solana wallet connect). App ID ships to the client; the secret
# is server-only and verifies wallets before any payout.
NEXT_PUBLIC_PRIVY_APP_ID=
PRIVY_APP_SECRET=
# The wallet rewards are paid FROM. Use a FRESH wallet whose private key
# has never been shared anywhere. This value is read only at runtime.
PAYOUT_WALLET_SECRET=
# Solana RPC for reading $THRONG balances (a private/paid RPC is best).
SOLANA_RPC_URL=https://api.mainnet-beta.solana.com
